args:
Today's Observer: Mitsuba

No matter how many times we called
his name, Pipple would not respond.
The pot's lid stayed firmly closed.
Hey! You haven't seen Pipple, have you?\nHe just handed us this seed and ran off.
He wanted these kids to learn how tasty\nvegetables could be—starting with him.
True. Being cooked is what he's\nalways wanted.
Rather than mourn his loss,\nwe should respect his resolve and\nhonor his wishes as only we can.
We have to cook him into the best\ndish possible! We have to change\nthe way they see vegetables forever!
Couldn't have said it better myself!
Huh? What are you talking about?\nWhere's Pipple?
He's on a very important mission—to help\nyou kids love veggies once and for all!
Here you are: one vegetable stew,\nloaded with local specialties. Bon appétit.
Urrrgh... It really IS all veggies.\nI don't wanna eat this...
Just try one bite. If that doesn't win you\nover, I won't force you to have more.
N-no way. It's super yummy!\nAre there really vegetables in here?!
The ones my mom used to use were never\nthis juicy.
Seasoning and technique make all the\ndifference. That, and having a secret\ningredient.
Thank you! Everything was sooo yummy!
I'll tell Mom to use this recipe, I promise!
Make sure to eat your greens so you\ngrow up big and strong, all right?
Okey dokey! Oh, but you never\ntold us where Pipple went.
He...returned to the forest.\nThe forest of life.
Aw, maaan! Then what should I do\nwith this seed?
I think you should try and plant it.\nThink of it as a memento of the\ntime you spent with Pipple.
Okay! I'll take really good care of it!\nThank you!

Today's Observer: Mitsuba

Our parting with Pipple was sudden
and bittersweet...but his pride as a
vegetable won out in the end.
We gave Pipple his wish.\nWe did the right thing.\nAnd so ends the Pipple Diary.
I half expected to see Pipple in the pot\nwhen I opened it. I miss him already...
No, I mean... Just come outside!
I suspect this Pipple came from the seed\nthe former Pipple left to the children.
Well, whatever the case, it's so good\nto have you back!
...Huh? Wait a second. Did I hear an echo\nor something?
Err, take a look over there.
Two, three, four...\nJust how many Pipples are there?!
That seed must have grown into\na whole crop of them.
Can one seed really produce THIS MANY?!\nIt's like there's a whole Pipple army!
Wheeee hee hee hee ha ha hoo!
My apologies, but this explanation\ndefies all reason.

Today's Observer: Kleimann

The little rascal has propagated most
ferociously! A shame his offspring are
making life difficult for the prince.
I've sent fifty Pipples to Hinomoto!
I've returned a hundred Pipples\nto the forest.
I lugged about fifty to each\nvillage with food shortages!
I left 150 Pipples in Picaro's restaurant.\nI'm sure he'll take care of them.
There are also three of the little\nscamps in my room! Whee hee hee!
Just don't do anything funny with 'em.\nWe've got Pipples for days already!
Phew... I think that's the Pipple problem\ndealt with. Good work, everyone.
You DO realize what a\nheadache you've been, right?
Look on the bright side. We learned\njust how selfless Pipple can be.
The people in all those villages\nwere overjoyed. Many lives will\nbe saved because of his actions.
I wonder if his mana's regenerative\nfunctions have other applications.\nThis calls for further testing!
None of this was a walk in the park—\nor the forest of life, as it were—\nbut all's well that ends well.
I'm glad we learned so much\nabout you, Pipple!

Today's Observer: Notte

Mitsuba's going to make some stock
from a Pipple to use in the cooking
contest. Can you say SLAM DUNK?

When we started this project, we had
no idea what Pipple was. Now one
thing is clear: he's a paragon of
veggie-hood through and through!
Well, that's it for the Pipple Diary!\nSweet dreams, veggie lovers!
